## Linting & Formatting

### ESLint Rules

ESLint rules enforced (errors block build):

- `jsx-a11y/alt-text`
- `jsx-a11y/anchor-has-content`
- `jsx-a11y/aria-props`
- `jsx-a11y/aria-role`
- `jsx-a11y/label-has-associated-control`
- `jsx-a11y/no-autofocus` (warning)

### Workflow

- Run `npm run lint` before committing
- Run `npm run format` to auto-fix formatting
- **After every task that touches source files, always run `npm run format` then `npm run lint` before finishing.**

### Prettier Configuration

- Prettier automatically sorts Tailwind CSS classes via `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`
- All formatting rules are defined in `.prettierrc`
- Format on save is recommended but not enforced

### Styling Conventions

- Tailwind CSS utility classes (sorted automatically by prettier-plugin-tailwindcss)
- CSS variable–based theme (defined in `app/globals.css`, consumed via Tailwind config)
- Class merging via `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`
- Minimal global styles (reset + typography only in `globals.css`)
